The paper presents a method to extract a weighted finite automaton (WFA) from a recurrent neural network (RNN), which involves machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves neural networks, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with control systems, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a less likely but still possible category.
